Two people
were killed and two others injured after a quarry where they were working
collapsed on them in Imenti South, Meru County. Confirming the incident, Imenti South Police Commander William Maronga said the four people were rushed to
Nkubu Consolata Hospital
but two were pronounced dead on
arrival.  The police
commander has called on
the relevant authorities to check on the
safety measures passed
by the security team on
the safety of Quarry Sites and Operators.  